President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Texas due to the conditions resulting from Tropical Storm Alex. The declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts in order to alleviate hardship and suffering. Federal assistance will be provided to save lives, protect property, and ensure public health and safety. The designated counties will receive equipment and resources necessary to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The federal government will provide 75% funding for emergency protective measures. Bradley Harris has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.